I"]<p>Using Docker, installation of the Xilinx Vivado tools can be automated and
easily transferred between machines.</p>

<h2 id="step-1-install-docker">Step 1 Install Docker</h2>
<p>You can either install Docker using the instructions <a href="http://phwl.org/2020/installing-docker/">here</a>.,
Docker can be installed either via the 
If you have not already installed Docker, I just used the Ubuntu package.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>apt-get update
<span class="nb">sudo </span>apt-get remove docker docker-engine docker.io

<span class="nb">sudo </span>apt <span class="nb">install </span>docker.io
<span class="nb">sudo </span>systemctl start docker
<span class="nb">sudo </span>systemctl <span class="nb">enable </span>docker
</code></pre></div></div>
